track.name: Don't Bother They're Here
comments: Can't describe the feeling. My favorite Stars of the Lid song (just this whole album in general really).
A true masterpiece. Reminds me alot of Eno's 1-1, from Music for Airports.

Mr_Tough

send in the clowns.. oh wait don't bother they're here. 

Shit, I only NOW realized that.
Good for pushing my Atman into Brahman.,.
fills a room with sound, like a bath of sunshine

"Obvious theft of Send In The Clowns. I'm surprised there were no copyright infringement lawsuits. Art or not,write your own."

Someone's a Streisand fan! hiyoooo
Which is funny, because she didn't write it either. No one who is famous for singing this song wrote it. This song has been performed by, what, at least five different recording acts, none of which are for whom it was written. 'Art or not, write your own' give me a break.

A brilliant de/reconstruction. These 'thieves' have taken a Sondheim track intended for Broadway, and turned it into the audio equivalent of floating in space. I love you, Stars of The Lid.
This track is truly a little night music
Send in the drones..............................................whether there here or your own or not.....just keep em coming.....
such a beautiful track! i like play it and my room is in the darkness. so fantastic.

Theft? Only if they hadn't obtained permission to sample Send In The Clowns. SOTL had written plenty of their own stuff. Nothing too unconventional with sampling once in a while. Damnit, I'm obsessed. I guess they're another one of those love 'em or hate 'em. Hmm.
send in the clowns.. oh wait don't bother they're here.
Obvious theft of Send In The Clowns. I'm surprised there were no copyright infringement lawsuits. Art or not,write your own.
Absolutely LOVE those drones from 1:53 to 3:30.
